# Ad network configuration. Leave NEXT_PUBLIC_AD_NETWORK unset or set to "none" before approval.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AD_NETWORK=none
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_PUB_ID=pub-5027420504477090

# ── Ticketmaster — Impact wrap URL template ─────────────────────────────────
# Format expected: <impact-wrap-base>?u={TARGET}&subId1={SHARED_ID}
# (or whatever Impact's link builder produces — the only contract is that the
# template contains the literal tokens {TARGET} and {SHARED_ID}).
#
# Generate from Impact dashboard: Discover > My Brands > Ticketmaster >
# Create A Link. Replace the destination URL portion with the literal string
# {TARGET}, and replace the SharedID field value with the literal string
# {SHARED_ID}. The runtime URL-encodes both before substitution.
#
# When unset, the Ticketmaster CTA links direct to ticketmaster.com without
# commission attribution (graceful pre-approval fallback — clicks still route
# correctly, they just aren't commissionable).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TICKETMASTER_IMPACT_WRAP=

# ── Deprecated env vars — affiliate programs not currently approved ─────────
# SeatGeek and StubHub were retired as ticket partners on 2026-05-03 in favor
# of single-source Ticketmaster. The URL builders in src/lib/affiliates.ts
# remain in the codebase (marked @deprecated) so legacy imports keep
# type-checking; restore these env values when direct brand approval lands.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SEATGEEK_AID=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STUBHUB_RID=
